setEdgeCode

private void setEdgeCode(Node sourceNode)
Sets the edge code for all edges which have the given node as source node if it is an XorSplitNode or LoopEndNode. Otherwise, no edge code is needed. The edge code is an integer starting from 0 which numbers all edges from the same source node.

Parameters:
sourceNode - set edge code for all edges with this node as source

setNodeIds

public void setNodeIds(Node node,
                       Node splitNode,
                       int branchId)
Description copied from interface: AristaFlowModel
Sets the IDs of the given node. IDs are topoId, branchId, SplitNode and CorrespondingBlockNode. TopoId is incremented and does not need to be passed to this method, CorrespondingBlockNode is set to the start node. CorrespondingBlockNode and SplitNode are not set for StartNode or EndNode.

Specified by:
setNodeIds in interface AristaFlowModel
Parameters:
node - Node where ID's need to be set
splitNode - Last AndNode or XorNode, @see AristaFlowModel
branchId - ID of the branch, @see AristaFlowModel

setNodeIds

public void setNodeIds(Node node,
                       Node splitNode)
Description copied from interface: AristaFlowModel
Sets the IDs of the given node. IDs are topoId, branchId, SplitNode and CorrespondingBlockNode. TopoId is incremented and does not need to be passed to this method, CorrespondingBlockNode is set to the start node. CorrespondingBlockNode and SplitNode are not set for StartNode or EndNode. BranchId is incremented automatically.

Specified by:
setNodeIds in interface AristaFlowModel
Parameters:
node - Node where ID's need to be set
splitNode - Last AndNode or XorNode, @see AristaFlowModel

createDataElementsForXorActivity

private DataEdge[] createDataElementsForXorActivity(Node splitNode,
                                                    NormalNode decisionNode,
                                                    java.lang.String[] conditions)
Creates DataElements and DataEdges needed for XorActivities. DataElements store the conditions and DataEdges connect them to the node where the condition is set (decisionNode).

Parameters:
splitNode - Node where XorActivity is assigned to
decisionNode - Node which is used to set conditions (decision node)
Returns:
array with created data edges
